<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,310,1868,1894]" box="[189,310,1868,1894]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1868,1894]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="114" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1868,1894]" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1915,2012]" lastBlockId="6.[188,1398,265,397]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="5" pageNumber="114">
Operculum completely divided into two free lobes. Two rows of opercular paleae. Outer paleae arranged in semicircles; straight, cylindrical, or slightly compressed blade with transverse irregular thecae bands. Few inner paleae arranged in one short row near to dorsal junction of inner marginal lobes, with straight and cylindrical blades. One or more pairs of nuchal spines. Tentacular filaments arranged in single rows (simple). Palps grooved, longer than operculum. Median ridge short with some lateral eyespots. Median organ absent. Four parathoracic segments (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[1004,1162,335,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Capa M. &amp; Hutchings P." pageId="6" pageNumber="115" pagination="144 - 163" refId="ref14623" refString="Capa M. &amp; Hutchings P. 2019. Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865. In: Helmcke J. G., Starck D., Wermuth H., Purschke G., Boggemann M. &amp; Westheide W. (eds) Handbook of Zoology, Annelida, Vol. 2: Pleistoannelida, Sedentaria II: 144 - 163. De Gruyter, Berlin, Germany." type="journal article" year="2019">Capa &amp; Hutchings 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,303,436,462]" box="[189,303,436,462]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,436,462]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,436,462]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[188,1399,482,720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authority="Kirtley, 1994" authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[189,558,482,509]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,396,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Mariansabellaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[403,558,482,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
included, until now, only four species: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stromgren, 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Stromgren" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[1018,1399,483,509]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="norvegica">
<emphasis box="[1018,1174,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">M. norvegica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stromgren T." box="[1190,1390,483,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref15284" refString="Stromgren T. 1971. A new species of Phalacrostemma (Annelida Polychaeta: Sabellariidae) from the Norwegian west coast. Kongelige Norske videnskabers selskabs skrifter 14: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1971">Strømgren, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Norwegian Sea, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirtley, 1994" authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[490,777,518,544]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="chilena">
<emphasis box="[490,615,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">M. chilena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[623,777,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[956,1022,518,544]" name="Chile" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Chile</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirtley, 1994" authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1034,1335,518,544]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="harrisae">
<emphasis box="[1034,1172,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">M. harrisae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[1180,1335,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Santa Monica Bay, California, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirtley, 1994" authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[599,899,553,579]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenhovei">
<emphasis box="[599,737,553,579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">M. tenhovei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[744,899,553,579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Yaquina Bay, Oregon. It is necessary to re-describe the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[520,727,588,614]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[520,727,588,614]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Mariansabellaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because Kirtley did not include the same characters in all species descriptions. Standardization in the descriptions will facilitate the identification and comparison of the species, and will also allow the development of identification keys with clearer and easier to observe characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
